OL,5, Cyclists who kill pedestrians could    
OL,6, face tougher sentences under a planned 
OL,7, new law for England.                   
OL,9,FThe move proposed by Transport         
OL,10,FSecretary Grant Shapps would close a   
OL,11,Floophole which means they can only     
OL,12,Fcurrently be jailed for two years.     
OL,14,FHe said it would "impress on cyclists  
OL,15,Fthe real harm they can cause when speed
OL,16,Fis combined with lack of care".        
OL,18,FA man whose wife was killed by a       
OL,19,Fcyclist said a new law could "bring a  
OL,20,Fdegree of comfort to relatives".       
